The paper discusses dataflow matrix machines, which are a generalization of recurrent neural networks. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. Additionally, the paper discusses programming patterns, which suggests that it could also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category. The paper also discusses the expressive power of dataflow matrix machines, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper discusses the network nature of the platform, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. The order of likelihood is based on the prominence of neural networks and machine learning in computer science research, followed by programming languages, artificial intelligence, and systems and control.
